snippet.textDisplay: She was able to say that because of a Caribbean sensibility. Compared to what we see on the North American stage, it's almost amazing what we take for granted living in the islands. I say almost because we just live, anybody is anybody, black, white, yellow, red... skin colour never affects us. Different races go to school, work, socialise, marry, intermarry. No big thing. So it's always amazing and difficult to reconcile this hatred for each other because of what? Skin colour? Just can't get over that. Sounds so silly and nonsensical. Each day most of us wonder: Can people really be so foolish?
